Description: Fragment of rim and rather steep shoulder of East Greek grey ware pottery dinos; dark brownish grey fabric with mica and limestone inclusions; dark slip on exterior.
Curator's comments: Sherd joins British Museum 1924,1201.60, which in turn joins 1888,0601.626 and Oxford AN1896-1908-G.122.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.046)
